⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of R₀
node POP · POP · ⟦R₀:POP:9cedf4⟧

WHO   — R₀ — the reproduction number · 1 − 1/R₀
WHAT  — The single number that says whether an outbreak grows (R₀ > 1) or dies (R₀ < 1), and sets the herd-immunity threshold 1 − 1/R₀.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because one number governs the whole arc of a contagion's spread.
HOW   — By counting onward transmissions — but it is context-dependent (density, contacts, method), not a fixed biological constant.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Above one, I grow; below one, I die. Vaccinate 1 − 1/me of the population and I can't catch — but I am not the constant people think.

